1. What is a prototype?
Solution : C. A low-fidelity manifestation of an idea, meant to be tested

2. Why should you create a Minimum Loveable Product (MLP) versus a Minimum Viable Product?
Solution : A. To truly delight your most loyal customers and ensure immediate adoption, versus solving the problems of all your customers, who may take more effirt to reach

3. Which tactics will help you rapidly prototype your MLP?
Solution : D. Use visual icons to express functionality, such as a magnifying glass for search
